note: Heyward is set to be sidelined eight or more weeks following surgery. One of the rare DTs who can outproduce most DE's, Heyward's loss is a big blow to the Pittsburgh Steelers and fantasy managers alike. Pittsburgh will employ a rotation in his stead, starting with placing DeMarvin Leal beside Larry Ogunjubi.

Marcus Williams is set to be sidelined for at least a few weeks, and a trip to IR has not been ruled out. Williams leaves a big DB1-sized hole on IDP rosters. Ar'Darius Washington and Geno Stone will fill in while he is sidelined.
